The new file preview mode allows to place comment pins anywhere in the previewed content, ie. a PDF file. Collaborating with your team in this way is great, but there are instances when you have to discuss this document with people not using Confluence (probably in a place where you don't have access to the Confluence server), and the comments you and your team already made in this document are essential for this discussion.

Please add an ability to export the file along with the comments, perhaps to a PDF file. This could be achieved by some sort of embedding/overlay of the comment pins (along with an automatic numbering), and printing the comment summary (ie. the actual comments) with corresponding numbers on an additional page.

